'''Bae Jun-ho''' ({{korean|배준호}}; born 21 August 2003) is a South Korean professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[left winger]] for {{English football updater|StokeCty}} club [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].

Bae began his professional career with [[Daejeon Hana Citizen]], helping them gain promotion to [[K League 1]] in the [[2022 K League 2|2022 season]]. After impressing in his debut season in the Korean top flight and for the [[South Korea national under-20 football team|South Korea U20]] team, he moved to European football with English [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] in August 2023.

==Club career==
===Daejeon Hana Citizen===
[[File:배준호vs FC 서울.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Bae Jun-ho with [[Daejeon Hana Citizen]] in 2023.]]

Bae started his career in the academy of [[Daegu FC]]. Afterwards, he attended Daegu Banyawol Elementary School, Daeryun Middle School, Cheonan Jeil High School and Jinwee High School.<ref name=klp>{{K League player|20220097}}</ref> While playing for Pyeongtaek Jinwee, the football club of Jinwee High School, he was considered one of his country's best talents.<ref name=naver>{{cite web |url=https://n.news.naver.com/sports/kfootball/article/076/0003821879 |script-title=ko:K리그 스카우트 홀린 '대전의 슈퍼루키' 배준호를 주목하라 |trans-title=Pay attention to 'Daejeon's super rookie' Bae Jun-ho, who was possessed by K League scout |date=13 January 2022 |accessdate=2 June 2023 |website=[[Naver]] |publisher=[[Sports Chosun]] |language=Korean}}</ref> In January 2022, following interest from a number of clubs across Europe, as well as former club Daegu, he signed for [[K League 2]] side [[Daejeon Hana Citizen]].<ref name=naver/> He made eleven appearances in his first season with Daejeon as he helped his team win the promotion play-offs against [[Gimcheon Sangmu]].<ref name=fifa>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/ko/articles/korea-republic-u-20-midfielder-bae-jun-ho-mixed-zone-interview-ko |script-title=ko:[서보원의 온 더 볼] U-20 대표 MF 배준호, "롤모델은 대전 선배 황인범" |trans-title=[Seo Bo-won's on the ball] U-20 international MF Bae Jun-ho, "My role model is Daejeon senior Hwang In-beom" |date=15 April 2023 |accessdate=2 June 2023 |publisher=FIFA |language=Korean}}</ref> In the [[2023 K League 1|2023 season]], Bae received more playing time in [[K League 1]], as he continued his integration into the squad from the reserve team.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.starnewskorea.com/stview.php?no=2023042706001240978 |script-title=ko:[현장목소리] '데뷔 2년 차' 대전 배준호의 패기, "아직 다 안 보여줬어" |trans-title=[Voice from the scene] 'a sophomore' Daejeon Bae Jun-ho's spirit, "I haven't shown everything yet" |date=27 April 2023 |accessdate=2 June 2023 |publisher=Starnews Korea |language=Korean}}</ref> On 27 August 2023, Daejeon officially announced that they had reached an agreement with [[EFL Championship]] side [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] for the transfer of Bae on a permanent deal.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Joo |first=Dae-eun |date=28 August 2023 |script-title=ko:'대전의 아들'이 '남자의 팀'으로 배준호, 스토크 시티 이적을 위해 출국 "항상 꿈꿔왔던 순간..최종 목표는 빅리그 진출" |url=https://sports.news.naver.com/news?oid=139&aid=0002188484 |access-date=28 August 2023 |website=[[Naver]]|publisher=Sportalkorea  |language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Bulley |first=Jim |date=28 August 2023 |title=Bae Jun-ho flies to Britain to sign with Stoke City |url=https://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/2023-08-28/sports/football/Bae-Junho-flies-to-Britain-to-sing-with-Stoke-City/1856437 |access-date=28 August 2023 |website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]}}</ref>

===Stoke City===
On 31 August 2023, Bae joined [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] for an undisclosed fee on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bae Junho joins the Potters |url=https://www.stokecityfc.com/news/2023/august/31/bae-junho-joins-the-potters/ |website=Stoke City |date=31 August 2023 |access-date=31 August 2023}}</ref> He scored his first goal in English football on 24 February 2024 in a 2–1 defeat against [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] and followed this up a week later in a 2–0 victory against [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Cardiff City 2–1 Stoke City: Cardiff hold on to end horrible home form |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/68324105 |website=BBC Sport |date=24 February 2024 |access-date=6 June 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Stoke 2–0 Middlesbrough: Potters breathe life into survival fight |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/68389102 |website=BBC Sport |date=2 March 2024 |access-date=6 June 2024}}</ref> In the [[2023–24 Stoke City F.C. season|2023–24 season]], Bae made 40 appearances as Stoke successfully avoided relegation, finishing in 17th position.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Smith |first1=Pete |title=Pete Smith's Stoke City end of season player ratings for 35-man squad |url=https://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/stoke-city-season-player-ratings-9272394 |website=Stoke Sentinel |date=9 May 2024 |access-date=7 June 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Southampton 0–1 Stoke City |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/68862287 |website=BBC Sport |date=27 April 2024 |access-date=7 June 2024}}</ref> He was named the [[Stoke City F.C. Player of the Year|club's Player of the Year]] in his first season at Stoke City.<ref name="stoke"/> In the [[2024–25 Stoke City F.C. season|2024–25 season]] Bae was a regular starter under three different managers, playing 49 times as Stoke avoided relegation on the final day.<ref>{{cite web |title=Stoke City end of season player ratings from sustained excellence to won't be seen again |url=https://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/stoke-city-season-player-ratings-10172075 |website=Stoke Sentinel |date=11 May 2025 |access-date=24 May 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Derby County 0–0 Stoke City: Both teams survive after goalless draw |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/derby-county-vs-stoke-city/509886 |website=Sky Sports |access-date=24 May 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Derby County 0–0 Stoke City |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cddelqp53ygt |website=BBC Sport |access-date=24 May 2025}}</ref> Bae was again a regular in [[2025–26 Stoke City F.C. season|2025–26]] under [[Mark Robins]], making 45 appearances but he came in for criticism for his lack of goals and assists.<ref>{{cite web |title=Stoke City 2025/26 squad review - keep, sell, loan, return or buy |url=https://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/stoke-city-transfer-keep-sell-10937317 |website=Stoke Sentinel |access-date=21 May 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=What Mark Robins wants to see from Bae Junho to hit Stoke City heights |url=https://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/stoke-city-bae-junho-watford-10866608 |website=Stoke Sentinel |access-date=23 May 2026}}</ref> 

==International career==
After representing South Korea at under-19 level in a number of friendlies, Bae was called up to the under-20 squad for the [[2023 AFC U-20 Asian Cup qualification]]. Having scored in two qualifiers against [[Mongolia national under-20 football team|Mongolia]] and [[Malaysia national under-20 football team|Malaysia]], he was called up to the [[2023 AFC U-20 Asian Cup]].<ref name=kfa>{{cite web |url=https://www.kfa.or.kr/archive/player_record.php?search_val=%EB%B0%B0%EC%A4%80%ED%98%B8 |title=Bae Jun-ho |access-date=1 June 2024 |publisher=KFA |language=Korean}}</ref> Although South Korea failed to win the tournament by being knocked out in the semi-finals by [[Uzbekistan national under-20 football team|Uzbekistan]], Bae was still praised for his performances.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://isplus.com/article/view/isp202303070151 |script-title=ko:U-20 아시안컵서 빛나는 배준호...한국 축구 미래 밝다 |trans-title=Bae Jun-ho is shining at the U-20 Asian Cup... The future of Korean football is bright |date=8 March 2023 |accessdate=2 June 2023 |publisher=[[Ilgan Sports]] |language=Korean}}</ref>

Bae was called up to the under-20 squad for the [[2023 FIFA U-20 World Cup]]. He started quietly in the tournament, but South Korea finished fourth under his influence. When he scored one and provided an assist in a 3–2 victory against [[Ecuador national under-20 football team|Ecuador]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chosun.com/sports/football/2023/06/02/7WAXX7IKRREAFDJPV6REICI4EE/ |script-title=ko:특훈 통했다, 특급 룸메와 해냈다... 해결사 배준호의 부활 |trans-title=Special training succeeded, He achieved with his roommate... Solver Bae Jun-ho's revival |date=2 June 2023 |accessdate=2 June 2023 |website=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |language=Korean}}</ref> Ecuadorian manager [[Miguel Bravo]] described him as a "Brazilian".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/member-associations/france/articles/u20-world-cup-argentina-2023-andrey-bae-cowell-daga-herdman-matturro-paez-pafundi-romero-slonina |title=Argentina 2023 graduates set for the FIFA World Cup 2026 |publisher=FIFA |date=12 June 2023 |access-date=1 June 2024}}</ref> Italian manager [[Carmine Nunziata]] defeated South Korea in the semi-finals, but he was also attracted to Bae's performance.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/stoke-transfer-bae-jun-ho-8695038 |title=Bae Jun-ho to Stoke City transfer latest as 'negotiations confirmed' |publisher=Stoke-on-Trent Live |date=22 August 2023 |access-date=1 June 2024}}</ref>

On 6 June 2024, Bae scored a goal in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC second round|FIFA World Cup qualifier]] against [[Singapore national football team|Singapore]], where he made his [[South Korea national football team|senior]] international debut.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=ESPN |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/687411/ |title=Singapore v South Korea game report |date=6 June 2024}}</ref> In May 2026, he was selected for the South Korea squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/south-korea-squad-world-cup-2026/blt15c57f5be1972d9b |title=South Korea squad World Cup 2026: Which players have made it to the showpiece in USA, Mexico and Canada? |publisher=Goal |date=2026-05-16 |access-date=2026-05-26}}</ref>

==Style of play==
An [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] who is comfortable using both feet, Bae has been regarded for his passing range and dribbling, as well as his balance and stamina.<ref name=naver/>

==Personal life==
Bae has cited fellow South Korean [[Hwang In-beom]], as well as [[Kevin De Bruyne]], as his biggest footballing role-models.<ref name=fifa/>

